= photons sr−1 cm−2 nm−1 s−1 * pixelarea * spectral bandwidth * fraction of solid angle with g1 = the spectral bandwidth of one spectral pixel; rowsum = spectral bandwidth (number of spectral pixels summed); f# = f-number. The pixel solid angle is given by pixelarea/f2 = 3.38*10− 6/f2 [sr] with f = focal length, the conversion of solid angle to square degrees is 1 sr = 3.283*103 [deg2] and pixel square degree is (3.38*10− 6 * 3.283*103)/f2 = 0.0111/f2 [deg2/pixel], thus:3photonsdeg2s-1=DN∗λ∗g1∗rowsum∗f2∗2π∗(1-cos(1/2f#))∗3.061103\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
